VLeela: The Path of The PlayfulIsha Foundation;Produced and marketed by AmuthamMusic Pvt. Ltd;8-DVD pack; Rs. 1,500Even as Yaksha, a seven-day music and dance programme organised by the Isha Yoga Foundation, is on at the foothills of the Velliangiri mountains, Coimbatore, till March 2, Amutham Music Pvt. Ltd. has produced an eight-DVD pack titled &#8216;Leela: The Path of the Playful' featuring talks on spirituality and life by Jaggi Vasudev.The DVDs are recordings of a programme held in September 2005, where the guru led a group on a journey to explore the multifarious dimensions of Krishna. This collector's edition draws you in to the world of Krishna.The foundation has also brought out DVDs (Rs. 100 each) which feature a series of discourses and Q&amp;A sessions with the guru. Some of the titles are &#8216;Guru: the Inner Awakening', &#8216;Mystic Wisdom' and &#8216;Heaven or Hell: It's Your Choice.'
